<p class="txt" id="font_text"/><p>THIRUVANANTHAPURAM: NIMS medicity has introduced wireless capsule endoscopy, a new diagnostic tool for the detection of small bowel disease non-invasively. </p><p class="txt" id="font_text">�This technique does not require insertion of endoscope through the mouth.</p><p class="txt" id="font_text">�Instead of lying down still on an examination table during the exam, patients can walk after the ingestion of the pill. </p><p class="txt" id="font_text">People while using wireless endoscopy can walk, sit and even return to normal work while the capsules are recording images. </p><p class="txt" id="font_text">�It is also disposable and therefore comfortable to patients.</p>&#13;
